@node "What_do" "What does the program do?"

                          @{fg highlight}Destination of program@{fg text}

  SystemReset is a simply program written in assembler which destination is
to reset your Amiga.

@endnode

@node "Description" "Description"

                               @{fg highlight}Description@{fg text}

  Program can be run from CLI/Shell or by clicking on its icon.
  Program ask user what to do and act according to the answer.
If user chose Reset program will reset your Amiga, if user chose
Cancel program will do nothing.

@endnode

@node "Requirements" "Requirements"

                                 @{fg highlight}Requirements@{fg text}

    To work program needs at least Kickstar 2.0 (v37) and reqtools.library
V2 (v38).

@endnode

